    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>In a hexagonal close-packed (hcp) unit cell, there are a total of 6 atoms present:</p>\n\n<p></p><p>2 atoms fully inside the unit cell (one at the top and one at the bottom layer)</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>12 atoms at the vertices, each shared with six other unit cells, contributing $1 / 6$ per atom</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>2 atoms in the middle layer, each shared with two other unit cells, contributing 1/2 per atom</p><p></p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1ma3uo638/f917c7a3-f567-4dd2-bc92-b90413fbdefe/dd557940-25b5-11f0-b83d-2702e74f88d9/file-jaoe38c1ma3uo639.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1ma3uo638/f917c7a3-f567-4dd2-bc92-b90413fbdefe/dd557940-25b5-11f0-b83d-2702e74f88d9/file-jaoe38c1ma3uo639.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IAT (IISER) 2020 Chemistry - Solid State Question 1 English Explanation\">",
